Sure, here are some example sentences using the Serbian word "bazen" in different forms and positions:

1. *Bazen* je prepun dece. (The *pool* is full of children.)
2. Moja devojka obožava da pliva u *bazenu*. (My girlfriend loves to swim in the *pool*.)
3. Ovaj *bazen* je veoma dubok. (This *pool* is very deep.)
4. Prošlog leta sam posetio nekoliko *bazena* u inostranstvu. (Last summer, I visited several *pools* abroad.)
5. Nadam se da ćeš se zabaviti na žurci pored *bazena*. (I hope you will have fun at the pool party.)
6. *Bazen* je pun vode. (The *pool* is full of water.)
7. Letos smo kupili novi *bazen* za dvorište. (This summer we bought a new *pool* for the backyard.)
8. Danas je previše hladno za plivanje u otvorenom *bazenu*. (Today it's too cold to swim in an outdoor *pool*.)
9. Deca su se utrkivala ko će prvi stići do *bazena*. (The kids raced to see who would get to the *pool* first.)
10. *Bazen* će biti zatvoren zbog održavanja. (The *pool* will be closed for maintenance.)

(Note: The word "bazen" in each sentence is marked with an asterisk (*) for clarity.)